03/03/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Croatian Prime Minister Ivo Sanader met with a NATO Parliamentary Assembly delegation on Tuesday (2 March) to discuss Croatia's integration into the North Atlantic structures.
The delegation was led by Chairman of the Assembly's Defence and Security Subcommittee Vahit Erdem.
Erdem expressed support for Croatia's integration efforts and pledged assistance.
Sanader said Croatia would make full preparations to join NATO in 2006 and the EU in 2007 or 2008.
(HINA - 02/03/04)
